article.linkText: Utah Tech takes down Cal Baptist 72-69
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. -- — Beon Riley had 21 points in Utah Tech's 72-69 win against Cal Baptist on Wednesday night. Riley added seven rebounds and three steals for the Trailblazers (5-3, 2-0 Western Athletic Conference). Jaylen Searles added 15 points while finishing 7 of 13 from the floor, and grabbed seven rebounds. Larry Olayinka was 5-of-6 shooting and 1 of 3 from the free-throw line to finish with 11 points. Dominique Daniels Jr. finished with 30 points, four assists and two steals for the Lancers (6-2, 1-1). Yvan Ouedraogo added nine points, 10 rebounds and two steals for Cal Baptist. In addition, Brantly Stevenson had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
